## Performance Optimization for All Devices

### Image Optimization
- Use WebP format with fallbacks
- Lazy loading with Intersection Observer
- Responsive images with srcset:
```html
<img 
  srcset="event-sm.webp 400w, event-md.webp 800w, event-lg.webp 1200w"
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 50vw, 33vw"
  src="event-lg.webp"
  alt="Event"
/>
```
- Skeleton loaders during image load
- Blur placeholder (LQIP - Low Quality Image Placeholder)

### Code Optimization
- **Code splitting**: Route-based lazy loading
```typescript
const EventDetail = lazy(() => import('./pages/EventDetail'));
const Checkout = lazy(() => import('./pages/Checkout'));
```
- **Bundle size**: Tree-shaking, remove unused dependencies
- **Memoization**: React.memo for expensive components
```typescript
const EventCard = React.memo(({ event }) => { ... });
```

### Data Loading
- **React Query** for caching and background updates
- **Optimistic updates**: Show changes immediately
- **Infinite scroll**: Load more events on demand
- **Prefetching**: Preload next page while user scrolls
- **Debounced search**: Wait 300ms after typing stops

### Mobile-Specific Optimization
- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44x44px
- **Reduce animations**: Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- **Virtual scrolling**: For long lists
- **Service Worker**: Cache static assets (PWA)
- **Compress API responses**: GZIP

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements focusable
- Visible focus indicators (2px outline)
- Skip to main content link
- Escape key closes modals/sheets
- Arrow keys navigate carousels

### Screen Readers
- Semantic HTML (header, nav, main, aside, footer)
- ARIA labels on icons and buttons
```html
<button aria-label="Add to favorites">
  <Heart aria-hidden="true" />
</button>
```
- ARIA live regions for dynamic content
- Descriptive alt text for images

### Color & Contrast
- Text contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1
- Interactive elements ≥ 3:1 against background
- Don't rely on color alone (use icons + text)
- Support dark mode

### Forms
- Labels associated with inputs
- Error messages announced to screen readers
- Required fields indicated
- Error summary at top of form

